quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,118,"Then judge between me and them with decisive judgement and save me and those with me of the believers."
  26,119,"So We saved him and those with him in the laden ship."
  26,120,"Then We drowned thereafter the remaining ones."
  27,91,"[Say, O Muḥammad], ",footnotes:1:[Or region, meaning Makkah and its surroundings.]
  27,92,"And to recite the Qur’ān."
  27,93,"And say, "
  28,64,"And it will be said, "
  28,65,"And [mention] the Day He will call them and say, "
  28,66,"But the information{1} will be unapparent to them that Day, so they will not [be able to] ask one another.",footnotes:1:[By which they might invent lies or excuses.]
  29,31,"And when Our messengers [i.e., angels] came to Abraham with the good tidings,{1} they said, ",footnotes:1:[Of the birth of Isaac and his descendant, Jacob.]
  29,32,"[Abraham] said, "
  29,33,"And when Our messengers [i.e., angels] came to Lot, he was distressed for them and felt for them great discomfort.{1} They said, ",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 11:77.]
  30,10,"Then the end of those who did evil was the worst [consequence] because they denied the signs of Allāh and used to ridicule them."
  30,11,"Allāh begins creation; then He will repeat it; then to Him you will be returned."
  30,12,"And the Day the Hour appears the criminals will be in despair."